      <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">XML</skos:prefLabel>
      <skos:definition xml:lang="en">XML – Extensible Markup Language – is a markup language that defines a set of rules for encoding documents in a format that is both human-readable and machine-readable. The design goals of XML emphasize simplicity, generality and usability across the Internet.</skos:definition>
      <dc:identifier>XML</dc:identifier>
      <atold:op-code>XML</atold:op-code>
